<div class="text-center">
  <h1>Quotes API</h1>
  <h2>Easily add random quotes to your website</h2>
</div>

<h3>Example with existing library</h3>
<p>You can use Quotes API as an iframe or with jQuery.</p>
<p>For a library of math quotes called "math":</p>
<h4>iframe</h4>
<code>
  &lt;iframe src=&quot;https://quotes.herokuapp.com/libraries/math/iframe&quot;&lt;/iframe&gt;
</code>
<h4>jQuery</h4>
<p>Suppose you have a div element that you want to contain a quote:</p>
<pre>&lt;div id=&quot;quote&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</pre>
<p>This is the jQuery script to put a quote in that div:</p>
<pre>
&lt;script&gt;
  $(function() {
    $.get(&quot;https://quotes.herokuapp.com/libraries/math/random&quot;, function(data) {
      $(&quot;#quote&quot;).html(data);
    });
  });
&lt;/script&gt;
</pre>
<h3>
  <%= link_to "Sign up", new_user_registration_path %> to add your own quote libraries
</h3>
<p>A public library can be viewed by anyone. A private library can only be viewed by its owner.</p>
<p>You can also add a <code>max_chars</code> param to the iframe or jQuery version to set a maximum length for returned quotes:</p>
<pre>&lt;iframe src=&quot;https://quotes.herokuapp.com/libraries/math/iframe?max_chars=20&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</pre>
<p>will only return full quotes (text and author) whose length is at nost 20 characters.</p>
